> just to check, is this changing behaviour? or just additional tests / faster implementation? (as I don't fully understand the link with the failing tests)

nothing changed. I *thought* it was doing something incorrectly, but appears to be ok. in py2.7-32 something is going wrong occasionally, not sure what exactly.
